{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"By experimentation with smaller numbers of urns and balls "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"(7,3)(9,3)(7,5)(9,5)"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"text","text":" I discovered that the number of urns(2013), doesn't matter to the average as long as it is more than the number of balls picked. Therefore, we can look at the average as if there were only 14 urns. Then for the 1st and 14th urns, the probability would be 1, and for the other urns it would be 0. "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2/14=1/7"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":" 1+7=8"}],"attrs":{"inline":false}}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let S be the number of ways to pick 13 balls of the same color, and T be the number of ways to choose 13 balls of any color. We are looking for "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\frac{S}{T}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". There are 2013 urns, and "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{2012 \choose 13}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ways to select 13 balls from an urn of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{i-1}+{2013+i}=2012"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" balls, so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"T=2013{2012 \choose 13}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Split S into W, the number of ways to select 13 white balls, and B, the number of ways to select 13 black balls. "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"S=W+B"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". There are "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{13 \choose 13}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ways to select 13 white balls from urn 14, "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{14 \choose 13}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ways to select 13 white balls from urn 15, all the way up to "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{2012 \choose 13}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ways for urn 2013. We are looking for "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\sum_{i=14}^{2013}{{i-1 \choose 13}}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", which by the hockey stick identity, is "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{2013 \choose 14}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". By the same process, "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"B={2013 \choose 14}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" as well. Therefore, "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"S=2{2013 \choose 14}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\frac{S}{T}=\frac{2{2013 \choose 14}}{2013{2012 \choose 13}}=\frac{2*2013}{2013*14}=\frac{1}{7}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a+b=8"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}
